The acting divisional commissioner of forensic services, Lieutenant General Mark Dumisa Magadlela, has been accused of misusing a state-owned vehicle and forging the signature of a junior officer. IPID spokesperson Moses Dlamini confirmed that the police watchdog was investigating a case of forgery, fraud, uttering, corruption, defeating the ends of justice and using a motor vehicle without the owner's consent. When contacted for comment, Magadlela said: "I can confirm that IPID investigated the allegations and it has made recommendations for disciplinary [action] to SAPS management." He declined to answer any other questions and referred News24 to IPID. WATCH: Police chopper corners home robber on N1 Motorists on the N1 south in Johannesburg, South Africa had their commute interrupted on Thursday as police flooded the motorway, to arrest a fleeing house robber. National police spokesperson Colonel Brenda Muridili said the matter was between the employer and employee, and that it was an internal one.  